0 EMOTE PMOTE PEMOTE~
Command:  emote/pmote/pemote <action>

The emote command is used to express emotions or actions for RP.  To use
it, type 'emote' followed by the action you want your character to portray. 
Using double-quotes around words in an emote will say them just as if you
were using the say command.  

The pemote command is exactly the same as emote except that it adds 's to
your name, so it can be used for possessive actions.  The pmote command
works the same as well, but if someone's name is in the emote, it will
replace it with 'you' for that character; for example, typing 'pmote bonks
Target on the head' will display as '<person> bonks you on the head' to
Target and '<person> bonks Target on the head' to everyone else.  
~

52 SMOTE~
Syntax: smote <action>

Smote works exactly like pmote, except you must place your name somewhere in
the string, and it will show that string to everyone in the room.
~

0 HOLD REMOVE WEAR WIELD~
Syntax: hold <object> Syntax: remove <object> Syntax: wear <object>
Syntax: wear all Syntax: wield <object>

Three of these commands will take an object from your inventory and start
using it as equipment.  HOLD is for light sources.  And WEAR is for armor. 
WIELD is for weapons.  

WEAR ALL will attempt to HOLD, WEAR, or WIELD each suitable item in your
inventory.  

You may not be able to HOLD, WEAR, or WIELD an item if it is too heavy for
you, or if you are not experienced enough to use it properly.  

REMOVE will take any object from your equipment and put it back into your
inventory.  
~

