0 'STUDY RESIDUE'~
Skill Type: Active (Residues Talent)
Command: studyresidue

The study residue skill allows you to learn weaves by observing the area
in which someone else has used the weave, allowing you to study and get a
sense of how it works.  Obviously, this only works on weaves used by members
of your own gender; men cannot study the residues of weaves from women, and
vice-versa.  

This skill can only be used in a room where someone of your gender has used
weaves, which is denoted by a message in the room saying 'You feel residues
of flows recently woven here!  ' When you see this message, use the
'raffects' command to see what weaves exist.  You will be able to see the
threads used (Air, Earth, Fire, Spirit and/or Water), the name of the weave
if you know it, and the number of ticks that the residue will remain.  Any
weave you do not know will display 'something' as the name.  Once this is
done, enter 'studyresidue' to try to figure out what the first 'something'
weave in the list is.  The skill can be used multiple times until you learn
the weave, and once you do, you will gain it for free at a skill level of 1.

Cost is not a factor when determining if you can learn a weave, so you can
study weaves that you do not actually have the spheres to cast.  However,
many weaves granted by talents will be difficult or impossible to learn with
this skill.  

One note: This skill IS NOT A REPLACEMENT for IC teaching!  If you gain a
weave with this skill that you do not or cannot have ICly (because you are
ICly just learning to use the Power or the like), you are advised to
restrict its use to OOC.  If it is found that this skill is being used to
gain weaves that a character should not have and then affects RP, there will
be consequences.  In addition, using this skill ICly while another person is
in the room should be emoted as such, because someone staring off into space
does tend to draw attention.  
