Initiates Combat: Yes
Used In Combat: No

The sap skill lets you attempt to strike another player or mob
unconscious, forcing them to sleep.  Players hit by this skill will not be
able to wake up for a few ticks until the sap effect wears off, while mobs
will remain sleeping; however, the target will immediately wake up if they
are attacked.  Training this skill makes it more likely that you will
successfully sap your target.  

Since the skill entails striking your target in the back of the head, it is
most easily done with a blunt weapon such as a mace or club.  Daggers carry
a slight penalty (striking the target with the hilt), and all other weapon
types carry a significant penalty.  

If you fail to sap your target, you will deal a small amount of damage to
them and they will immediately attack you, so be careful!  
