0 EMBRACE SEIZE CHANNEL CAST UNCHANNEL RELEASE~
Skill Type: Active
Command: embrace/seize/channel <amount>
         cast <weave>
         unchannel/release

The embrace and seize skills allow channeler to use Saidar and Saidin
respectively.  The 'channel' command is an alternate form that works for
either male or female characters.  Using the commands with a number will
cause you to hold exactly that amount of the Source (so 'channel 100' would
cause your character to hold 100 of the power, split based on your sphere
maximums).  You can enter a number higher than your spheretotal, but you
risk gaining burnout points.  Using the commands without a number will hold
an amount of the Source based on your 'autochannel' setting in your score
sheet.  As your skill increases, you reduce the possibility that you will be
unable to grasp the Source when needed.  

Embrace, seize and channel only cause you to grasp the Source, not do
anything with it.  To use a weave, use the 'cast' command with the weave
name.  If you are not holding the Source when using the cast command, you
will automatically embrace/seize based on your autochannel setting, just as
if you had used the embrace/seize command without entering a number, and
this attempt can fail just like using the command.  If you succeed, you will
attempt to cast the named weave.  For weaves with multiple-word names, the
weave name can be put in single-quotes, such as "cast 'arrows of fire'".  

The 'unchannel' and 'release' commands allow you to let go of the Source
once you have grasped it.  It is recommended that you do this often, as
holding the Source for too long puts you at risk of gaining burnout points. 
~

0 ENDURANE HITPOINTS HP~
ENDURANCE is the measure of your character's stamina and remaining
energy.  This is used for movement, combat, and when using the One Power.  

HITPOINTS are the measure of your character's health.  The lower your
character's hitpoints, the closer they are to fainting or perhaps death. 
Both mobs and players attacking your character creates the possibilty of a
lowering of your hitpoints, as well as being poisoned by berries or another
source.  

Both endurance and hitpoints can be trained up to a certain level during
your adventuring career.  It is recommended that such training be done at an
early level to impart the maximum benefit of the gains made during leveling.
~

