0 BOND BONDING~
Weave Type: Active
Command:  cast bond <player>

The bond weave is a weave of Spirit that creates a link between two
people.  It is used by Aes Sedai of the White Tower to take people as their
Gaidin, with both characters gaining increased ability and some other neat
perks.  

Now that you know that, here are the rules:

- The bond weave is a granted weave which will be given to Aes Sedai of the
White Tower ONLY.  Unless you are involved in an IMM-driven RP where it is
granted to your character, do not bother asking for it.  

- Bonding is an IC act, but it must be agreed upon by both parties OOCly. 
Forcing someone into a Bond ICly is allowed if the RP works in that manner
and the character OOCly agrees to be Bonded.  If a Bond is forced onto
someone OOCly, the Bond will be undone and the aggressor will be {RDELETED{x.  

- The bond weave is not to be taught to anyone who is not Aes Sedai, ICly or
OOCly.  If it is, both the teacher and the student will be {RDELETED{x.  

- Currently, you are not allowed to bond people who are members of the
Children of the Light.  Bonding a wolfkin, male channeler or member of the
same gender is allowed, but you will be expected to deal with the
ramifications and RP it accordingly.  This will be checked up on to
determine if it is being ignored.  

- Currently, unbonding or passing of bonds is not allowed.  Bonding is not
something to take lightly ICly or OOCly; once Bonded, both parties are tied
to each other until one of them dies.  An exception will be made to this
rule IF one of the Bonded pair does not log on their character for a period
of three REAL LIFE months for more than five hours.  If this occurs, the
Bonded PC who is left may petition to have the bond released, which will
result in the IC death of the character who has not logged on.  THIS MEANS
that if you agree to be Bonded, YOU AGREE that your character can and will
be deleted and to have your Bonded partner write a story about your death if
you do not log in for three months.  

- Currently, members of the Green Ajah are allowed no more than two Bonded,
and members of any other Ajah are allowed only one.  Members of the Red Ajah
are allowed to Bond, but their choice must be approved by the IMM staff.  

Bonding is not something to be taken lightly.  Consider your RP and what you
know about the person you are RPing with, and choose wisely.  
~

0 GAIDIN WARDER~
Aes Sedai have a weave which is learned upon becoming Aes Sedai which is
quite unique.  This weave, a composition of mainly Spirit, binds the Aes
Sedai to a man of her choice permanently.  In doing this, the man is given
the ability to heal quickly, to go without rest, food, or water for long
periods of time and the unique ability to sense the taint of the Dark One,
even froma distance.  As well, both Aes Sedai and her Warder, as they are
called, are given the ability to sense one another's state of health.  If
either dies, the other will sense it.  However, there is a difference, for
if the Aes Sedai should be the one to die, the Warder will lose his will to
live and seek death often times.  Very rarely are they able to be kept
alive.  

Warders are also know as Gaidin, a term which means Brother to Battles. 
They go into the bonding almost always voluntarily, though some have been
done against the Warder's will.  The loyalites of the Gaidin are completely
to their Aes Sedai, and they live where their Aes Sedai lives.  For example,
when on the grounds, the Gaidin remain in a special area, their own private
quarters closely set to the Tower.  

Gaidin's numbers are not dictated by Tower Law, however by tradition, a man
is not bonded to Red Aes Sedai ever.  Most other Ajahs, should they have a
Gaidin, remain with only one.  There is an exception, in that the members of
the Green Ajah tend to bond as many as they wish.  

While the closeness of the bond may seem to lend to a certain ammount of
intimacy, the relations are chaste a majority of the time.  Aes Sedai have
many pressures and demands upon them, and Warders tend to fall into the role
of guardian and protector most often.  As with anything, there is
exceptions, and Aes Sedai on very rare occasions have been known to marry
their Warder, however this has usually only happened amoung members of the
Green Ajah.  

(See also: BOND, GREENAJAH, WHITETOWER) 
 
