0 TYING TIE UNTIE~
Skill Type: Active
Command: tie <weave>/all <target>/room/ward
         untie <weave>/all <target>/room/ward

The tying skill allows a channeler to 'tie off' a weave that they are
sustaining on a person or the room.  Tying the weave means that it will
eventually fade away, but it also means that the channeler no longer has to
concentrate on it and can go elsewhere without the weave collapsing, such as
creating a wall of air and then moving on to keep it there to ward off foes.

The tying skill also allows channelers to attempt to untie weaves that have
been tied previously, either by themselves or someone else.  The difficulty
of this task depends on the tying skill of the person who tied it; training
the tying skill makes it much more difficult for others to untie your
weaves.  

Tying weaves on yourself or a target refers to weaves such as wrap that
apply to a person.  Tying weaves on the room refers to weaves such as wall
of air that apply to the room.  Tying wards refer to weaves such as
Shadowspawn ward or eavesdrop ward.  
~

